10 SECTION 9. G.S. 160D-403(c) reads as rewritten:
11 "(c) Duration of Development Approval. – Unless a different period is specified by this
12 Chapter or other specific applicable law, including for a development agreement, a development
13 approval issued pursuant to this Chapter expires one year after the date of issuance if the work
14 authorized by the development approval has not been substantially commenced. Local
15 development regulations may provide for development approvals of shorter duration for
16 temporary land uses, special events, temporary signs, and similar development. Local
17 development regulations may also provide for development approvals of longer duration for
18 specified types of development approvals. Nothing in this subsection limits any vested rights
19 secured under G.S. 160D-108 or G.S. 160D-108.1.G.S. 160D-108, G.S. 160D-108.1, or
20 G.S. 160D-108.2."
21 SECTION 10.(a) G.S. 160D-601, as amended by Section 3K.1(a) of S.L. 2024-57
22 reads as rewritten:
23 "§ 160D-601. Procedure for adopting, amending, or repealing development regulations.
24 …
25 (d) Down-Zoning. – No amendment to zoning regulations or a zoning map a zoning
26 regulation that down-zones property shall be initiated, enacted, or enforced without the written
27 consent of all property owners whose property is the subject of the down-zoning
28 amendment.amendment, unless the down-zoning amendment is initiated by the local
29 government.
30 (e) For purposes of this section, "down-zoning" or "down-zone" means a zoning
31 ordinance regulation that affects an area of land in one of the following ways:
32 (1) By decreasing the development density of the land to be less dense than was
33 allowed under its previous usage.
34 (2) By reducing the substantive permitted uses of the land that are specified in a
35 zoning ordinance or land development regulation to fewer uses than were
36 allowed under its previous usage.
37 (3) By creating any type of nonconformity on land not in a residential zoning
38 district, including a nonconforming use, nonconforming lot, nonconforming
39 structure, nonconforming improvement, or nonconforming site element."
40 SECTION 10.(b) This section is effective when it becomes law and applies
41 retroactively to December 11, 2024. Any development ordinance affected by Section 3K.1 of
42 S.L. 2024-57 shall be treated as if it remained in effect from June 14, 2024, to December 11,
43 2024.
44 SECTION 11. Except as otherwise provided, this act is effective when it becomes
45 law and applies to any nonconformity existing on or after December 11, 2024.
